  Bards are jacks-of-all-trades by nature.  If you like having a wide 
variety of abilities, this is the right guild for you.  However, in 
order to have this leeway, bards forfeit the opportunity to excel in 
any one field of expertise.  Bards are first and foremost entertainers, 
and their skills reflect those aspects of entertainment they can 
incorporate into other walks of life.
  Bards are fair to good fighters, being able to wear nearly any armor 
and wield any weapon.  Some of their special abilities do not function 
when wearing armor, for it is hard to be entertaining when you scare 
your audience.
  In their journeys, bards pick up the rudiments of mundane and 
magical learnings.  Being somewhat roguish in nature, they also have 
talents to get them by when entertaining is in a slump and times are 
lean.
  Although bards get along well with others, they would be foolish 
not to have learned self-reliance.  Thus, they are quite able to take 
care of themselves if they have to.
  In short, bards have all the benefits of being multi-classed without
any of the drawbacks, such as slower advancement.
  Since bards are "people-people", charisma is the most important 
attribute.
  If you have further questions, just ask a bard.  If you go south
from the center of town in Darkwind City, you'll soon find the
guild.  Adaon will be glad to help you out.
